<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>LALS&#160;268.  History of Central America.  3 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
The human and territorial characteristics of Central America, including facets of Spanish colonialism and the history of revolutions and modernity in the region, including a history of U.S. - Central American relations. Course Information: Same as <a href="/search/?P=HIST%20269" title="HIST&#160;269" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'HIST 269');">HIST&#160;269</a>. Prerequisite(s): Completion of the English composition requirement.<i>  Past course</i>.<br />
