<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>LALS&#160;272.  Brazil: A Multi-Ethnic Society.  3 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
The diverse political, economic, artistic, and folkloric themes of Brazilian life are traced in such national festivals as Carnaval and Sao Joao, and folk religions such as Candomble. Course Information: Same as ANTH 278. Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=ANTH%20101" title="ANTH&#160;101" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'ANTH 101');">ANTH&#160;101</a>; or consent of the instructor.<i>  Individual and Society course, and  World Cultures course</i>.<br />
